Interface TreeNode

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GroupNode, LeafNode

    public interface TreeNode
    This interface represent a TreeNode interface. A tree node could return whether it is a leaf node, get this node's symbol, and get children of this node.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.Map<java.lang.Character,TreeNode> getChild()
      Return this node's children as a Map object.
      char getSymbol()
      Return this node's symbol as a charactor.
      boolean isLeaf()
      Return true if this node is a leaf node, false otherwise.
